against RGZ Data Release 1 where a final test accuracy of 94.8 per cent
was obtained, using both original and augmented images. The use of sigma
clipping does not offer a significant benefit overall, except in cases
with a small number of training images.}, journal={Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society}, author={Lukic, V. and Brüggen, M. and Banfield, J. K. and Wong, O. I. and Rudnick, L. and Norris, R. P. and Simmons, B.}, year={2018}, month={May}, pages={246–260} }

